    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix cross-layer parameter mismatch in IF4p5 fronthaul processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `fh_if4p5_north_in` function was incomplete, causing inconsistent operation downstream. When `fh_north_asynch_in` was NULL (indicating synchronous processing), the `fh_north_in` function pointer remained unassigned, leading to cross-layer parameter mismatches between PHY, MAC, and RRC layers.\n\nThis fix assigns the function pointer and completes the implementation to match the asynchronous version's behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-ru.c`: \n  - Assigned `fh_if4p5_north_in` to `fh_north_in` in REMOTE_IF4p5 configuration\n  - Completed `fh_if4p5_north_in` implementation with proper frame/subframe validation\n  - Added RU internal state updates (tti_tx, frame_tx, timestamp_tx)  \n  - Added calls to downstream processing functions (feptx_ofdm, fh_south_out)\n\n### Reproduction\nSystems using REMOTE_IF4p5 configuration with synchronous processing would experience:\n- Segfaults when trying to call NULL function pointer\n- Frame/subframe mismatches causing processing errors\n- Downstream RU processing failures due to missing state updates\n- Inconsistent timing between layers leading to synchronization issues\n\nThe issue manifests as intermittent connection drops and incorrect signal processing in RRU deployments.\n"
}